                    },
                    "body": "Fixed by r24215",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guilhermeblanco",
                        "name": "guilhermeblanco",
                        "displayName": "Guilherme Blanco",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-08T21:32:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-08T21:32:09.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47526",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This change introduces new bugs which breaks existing functionalities.\r\nIt makes Zend_Translate unusable for directory scanning.\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-16T07:01:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-16T07:04:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47530",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think that can be used the option 'ignore' with values default.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-17T19:32:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-17T19:32:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47534",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guilhermeblanco",
                        "name": "guilhermeblanco",
                        "displayName": "Guilherme Blanco",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@thomas\r\nIn which cases does it break? I think it's possible to fix it.\r\nProblem is that E_FATAL happens during RecursiveIteratorIterator, so it's not possible to simply add it to ignore.\r\n\r\n\r\n@ramon \r\nNo way. The E_FATAL does not happen during RecursiveDirectoryIterator, but inside RecursiveIteratorIterator. The problem blows up internally, because it uses the FilterIterator, which is where it explodes.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guilhermeblanco",
                        "name": "guilhermeblanco",
                        "displayName": "Guilherme Blanco",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-18T00:44:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-18T00:44:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47610",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@guilherme \r\nSee a example of bc break http:\/\/pastebin.com\/VzpkZXk0.\r\nThe problem is with the option scan = directory, because after r24215 was deleted the second argument(the mode) of [RecursiveIteratorIterator::__construct()|http:\/\/www.php.net\/manual\/en\/recursiveiteratoriterator.construct.php] that was the following RecursiveIteratorIterator::SELF_FIRST.\r\nIs need return the parents too(dir) to that meets the condition (Zend_Translate_Adapter in line 276).\r\n\r\nGreetings,\r\nRamon\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-23T18:59:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-23T18:59:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47616",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As said directory scanning does not work anymore within the latest released version.\r\nThe language is not set which is caused by the BC you integrated within my component.\r\n\r\nSee the two linked issues for details on reproduction.\r\nSee pull request 259 for the fix within ZF2.\r\n\r\nPlease backport this fix within ZF1 to make this component work properly again.\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-24T19:44:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-24T19:44:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47633",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=croensch",
                        "name": "croensch",
                        "displayName": "Christoph Roensch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Ramon\nby reintroducing the RecursiveIteratorIterator flag it got Zend_Translate_Adapter_ArrayTest::testOptionLocaleDirectory() and all other Tests running again :)\n\n@Thomas\nI didn't quite understand that ZF2 pull request, so for simplicity may just apply this patch to the library.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=croensch",
                        "name": "croensch",
                        "displayName": "Christoph Roensch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-25T13:47:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-25T13:47:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47634",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guilhermeblanco",
                        "name": "guilhermeblanco",
                        "displayName": "Guilherme Blanco",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Thomas Your patch only fixes a small part of the problem.\r\nThere're some specific folders (like .cvs, .svn) that are not related to user customized ignore list. Your patch sounds valid to fix user issues, but not this one. We'd have to always include the ignore for these folders, that's why your PR is not useless. It can be used, for sure.\r\n\r\nI'm fixing the issue myself by applying the proposed patch of @Christoph.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guilhermeblanco",
                        "name": "guilhermeblanco",
                        "displayName": "Guilherme Blanco",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-25T14:44:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-25T14:44:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47635",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guilhermeblanco",
                        "name": "guilhermeblanco",
                        "displayName": "Guilherme Blanco",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed the issue in r24267 and merged to ZF 1.11 branch in r24268.\n\n@Thomas your proposal is still valid here, but since it does not refer to actual issue, but rather an enhancement to \"ignore\" support, I'm marking this ticket as resolved by now.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guilhermeblanco",
                        "name": "guilhermeblanco",
                        "displayName": "Guilherme Blanco",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-25T14:52:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-25T14:52:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47641",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Guilherme:\r\nYou seem not to understand what my change does and how it works nor how the component itself works in detail.\r\n\r\nThe ignore option has been added in past to prevent all \".\" directories from being scanned.\r\nThis includes per default also all other \".\" directories like \".hudson\" or the hidden \".\" directories from windows.\r\nOn the other hand a user can change the ignore option in a way that it still scans a \".svn\" or any other wished directory.\r\nThe \"ignore\" option prevents scanning for all directories BEGINNING with the given string. This includes \".svn\" and \".cvs\".\r\n\r\nYour change makes it impossible for a user to scan the directories he whishes to use. This is a potentional BC as it erases existing functionallities.\r\n\r\nOnly because I work on ZF2 and try to add additional benefits as component author does not mean that I don't know what I do.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-25T18:38:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-25T18:38:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47642",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guilhermeblanco",
                        "name": "guilhermeblanco",
                        "displayName": "Guilherme Blanco",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Thomas\r\nIt was never my intention on my words to sound like you don't know what you do. Quite the opposite.\r\n\r\nThe point I referred previously is that \"ignore\" option never worked well, mostly because the possible script break have already happened.\r\nTo be useful, the \"ignore\" option must be added between the RecursiveDirectoryIterator and RecursiveIteratorIterator, because it's in the latter that script breaks.\r\n\r\nI already saw your patch, and I agree with your proposal. The option to be part of RegExIterator is extremely valid, simplifying the operation of FilterIterator used internally by RecursiveIteratorIterator. Then again, that's why I mentioned to your your patch is still valid, because it fixes the \"ignore\" problem. But then again, \"ignore\" must still have default values and not only user values.\r\n\r\nBut getting stick to the bug, the reported issue is the missing flag on RecursiveIteratorIterator. For a simple solution, adding it is enough to have my issue fixed and recently opened ones fixed too. The enhancements related to \"ignore\" can be surely merged, but that is a bigger patch, which may take more time to me merged\/fixed.\r\n\r\nSorry, but it was never my intention to make you angry. I just want to have a patch that fixes my problem and also do not break existent functionality. I just don't wanted to have my issue reverted because it would solve some reported issues, but would make mine active again.\r\n\r\n\r\nCheers,",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=guilhermeblanco",
                        "name": "guilhermeblanco",
                        "displayName": "Guilherme Blanco",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-25T19:04:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-25T19:04:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47645",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm not angry.\r\n\r\nThe point is that the default value for the ignore option is \".\" since this feature has been added. This includes \".svn\" and \".cvs\" directories as those begin with \".\".\r\n\r\nBut default values must be overwriteable. This functionallity has been deleted by your change. That's what I wrote you about and what I was aware of for ZF2.\r\n\r\nAdditionally I would ask you not to take over issues which have been marked as in progress as this means that someone is already working on them.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-25T19:45:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-25T19:45:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49814",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Is there still an issue with the code introduced here?\r\nIf so, is it something that should be reverted for 1.12?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
